[h3 id=Introduction 
	"Introduction
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Degz is a fan remake of the arcade game 
	[a href=http://adb.arcadeitalia.net/?mame=scramble rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Scramble
	]a
	" by Konami. This fan remake was developed by 
	[a href=https://www.reboot-games.com/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Reboot
	]a
	" as, according to the title screen, an example game for their 
	[a href=https://reboot-games.com/raptor/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"RAPTOR API
	]a
	" for use in 
	[a href=https://reboot-games.com/jagstudio/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"JagStudio
	]a
	", a homebrew development tool for making Atari Jaguar and Jaguar CD games.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The game can be downloaded for free here: 
	[a href=https://www.reboot-games.com/rebootnews/degz/ rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"https://www.reboot-games.com/rebootnews/degz/
	]a
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"I've been tackling the All Platforms Challenge bit by bit, which is mainly an excuse for me to check out different console libraries. There's a standard Atari Jaguar port as well but I chose the Atari Jaguar CD version for a reason. The big problem with the Atari Jaguar CD is that there's less than 20 official releases for the add-on. I didn't quite get the interest to TAS those so I explored what was out there for Atari Jaguar homebrew and a few interesting games came up. I ended up choosing Degz since I do like Scramble and it's a very short and straightforward game.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=RunNotes 
	"Run notes
	$LF
]h3
